OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, The prime minister and the Home Office 
OL,6, have been criticised by the UK         
OL,7, statistics watchdog for incorrectly    
OL,8, claiming crime has fallen.             
OL,10,FSpeaking in the Commons on Monday,     
OL,11,FBoris Johnson said crime had come down 
OL,12,Fby 14% since he took office.           
OL,14,FIt followed a Home Office press release
OL,15,Flast week that claimed the government  
OL,16,F"continues to cut crime".              
OL,18,FThe UK Statistics Authority (UKSA) said
OL,19,Fthe prime minister "did not make clear"
OL,20,Fthe figure excluded fraud.             
